By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The latest COVID-19 report released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has it that Lagos State, the epicentre of the novel virus, accounted for 642 infections as the health agency confirmed 1,074 new cases on Monday. According to the report released via the agency’s twitter handle, the other 14 states (including FCT) where infections were recorded are:Kaduna-92; Rivers-78; FCT and Gombe-66 each; Kano-35; Ogun-31; Katsina-22; Plateau-20; Abia-7; Niger and Oyo-4; Akwa Ibom-3;Delta and Osun-2 each. The NCDC further informed that the total confirmed cases have risen to 88,587 out of which 74,373 patients have been treated and discharged since the index case was reported in February 27 in Nigeria. It also stated that 1,294 lives have been lost to COVID-19 related complications from across the various isolation facilities in Nigeria. The health agency gave the breakdown of the total confirmed cases by each of the 36 states of the federation (including the FCT) below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The total confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria hit 59,001 as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) reported 153 new fresh infections on Thursday. Similarly, the NCDC report released via it's twitter handle account further said that the total of 50, 452… October 2, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria on Saturday recorded 110 new cases of COVID-19 infections, bringing the total confirmed cases in the country to 67,330, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. This is also as the Centre has informed that a total of 62,819 patients have… November 29, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Lagos State, the epicentre of COVID-19 in Nigeria recorded 106 infections on Friday as the Centre for Disease Control confirmed 170 new cases of the novel virus. This renewed upsurge in number of infections in Lagos may not be unconnected with the larg